A walking colony of corrupted fungi that has assumed a roughly humanoid shape
using the skeleton of some long-dead creature as an armature. The spore husk
moves by releasing clouds of particles that interact with the mist's volatile
compounds, propelling its body through the fungal lattice corridors. Contact
with the spore cloud causes immediate respiratory distress and longer-term
confusion amplification.
~
