prism-leech swarm~
a prism-leech swarm~
A swarm of prism-leeches pulses with crystalline light.
~
Not a single creature but a colony of small, translucent organisms that move
in coordinated clouds. Each prism-leech is finger-length, its body suffused
with Conclave crystal fragments that refract light into disorienting prismatic
bursts. The swarm hunts by overwhelming prey with sensory overload: the
combined light display of hundreds of individual leeches creates a strobing
effect that paralyzes and disorients, allowing the colony to feed.
~
