A neogi that has achieved master status, identifiable by the barbed whip it
carries and the deference shown by lesser neogi in its presence. The master
is larger and sleeker than common neogi, its fur groomed and its movements
carrying the confidence of authority. Its long neck sways as it surveys its
domain, and its mandibles are stained with the chemical markers that enforce
its hierarchical position.
