#9644
mist cartographer~
the Mist Cartographer~
The Mist Cartographer studies the forest with intense concentration.
~
A weather-beaten figure in the remains of a Kiess survey captain's uniform,
its insignia still recognizable beneath years of forest grime. The Mist
Cartographer is a former Kiess officer who ventured too deep into the forest,
learned its logic, and refused to return. The captain's maps are drawn on
bark sheets, their notation incomprehensible to standard Kiess cartography
because they record the forest's shifting topology rather than static terrain.
The Cartographer's eyes are clear and sharp, carrying the focused intelligence
of someone who has mastered a problem that defeated an institution.
~
