E
compass cartographer mist~
The compass is hand-crafted from materials found in the forest: a wooden case,
a crystal needle, and a backing of mirrorbark. Unlike ordinary compasses,
this one does not point north. Instead, its needle tracks the forest's shifting
topology, pointing toward the nearest true path through the confusion. The
Mist Cartographer built it after learning the forest's logic, and it represents
a unique understanding of how the three-force overlap governs navigation.
~
